Class OnetimeService

  • java.lang.Object
    • cps.entities.models.OnetimeService
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ParkingService, java.io.Serializable

    public class OnetimeService
extends java.lang.Object
implements ParkingService
    Database entity for one-time parking services - incidental parking or reserved parking both stored in the same table.

      • findLateCustomers

        public static java.util.Collection<OnetimeService> findLateCustomers(java.sql.Connection conn,
                                                                     java.time.Duration delta,
                                                                     boolean warned)
                                                              throws java.sql.SQLException
        Find OnetimeService records where the customer is late to their reservation. Is used to warn customers that their scheduled reservation has started, and wait for a reply for 30 minutes. Is used again to retrieve a list of all the OnetimeService records that should be canceled because their customers did not respond to the warning within 30 minutes.
        Parameters:
        conn - the SQL connection
        delta - the time interval within which the starting time of the reservation should be located
        warned - whether to search records where the customer was already warned, or records where the customer has not been warned yet
        Returns:
        the collection
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException - on error
